<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,719,853]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">
The subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[315,472,720,744]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Polyblepharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,472,720,744]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">Polyblepharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1822" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[548,840,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicans">
<emphasis box="[548,675,720,744]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">E. albicans</emphasis>
Meigen, 
<number box="[784,840,720,744]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" value="1822.0">1822</number>
</taxonomicName>
as type-species) currently includes 
<number box="[1247,1275,720,744]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" value="70.0">70</number>
species. Only two species (
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[303,766,756,781]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandti">
<emphasis box="[303,419,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">E. brandti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev" box="[428,766,756,781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" refString="Shamshev, IV. &amp; Grootaert, P. (2005) New data on the genus Empis Linnaeus (Diptera: Empididae) from Iran, with descriptions of two new species. Studia dipterologica, 12 (1), 29 - 36." type="journal article" year="2005">
Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 
<number box="[710,766,756,781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[826,1303,756,781]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Empis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turanica">
<emphasis box="[826,955,757,780]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">E. turanica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev" box="[964,1303,756,781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" refString="Shamshev, IV. &amp; Grootaert, P. (2005) New data on the genus Empis Linnaeus (Diptera: Empididae) from Iran, with descriptions of two new species. Studia dipterologica, 12 (1), 29 - 36." type="journal article" year="2005">
Shamshev &amp; Grootaert, 
<number box="[1245,1303,756,781]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[319,364,792,815]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shamshev" box="[380,711,791,816]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" refString="Shamshev, IV. &amp; Grootaert, P. (2005) New data on the genus Empis Linnaeus (Diptera: Empididae) from Iran, with descriptions of two new species. Studia dipterologica, 12 (1), 29 - 36." type="journal article" year="2005">
Shamshev &amp; Grootaert 
<number box="[650,711,791,816]" pageId="6" pageNumber="191" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). We found for the first time four other species of this subgenus from 
<collectingCountry box="[212,261,829,852]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="191">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
